Package interfaces

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BrakeInterface
    The brake interface represents the only means by which the EHB can modulate the brake pressure.
    ButtonInterface
    NOTE :: Almost no button state is maintained by this class.
    GearInterface
    The gear interface provides a very simple means to check which gear the car is currently in.
    SpeedInterface
    This interface provides a way to query the current speed of the car in meters per second.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ButtonColorTypes
    This enum represents the set of valid color types that can be used to set the color of the brake button.
    ButtonSoundTypes
    This enum represents the set of sounds that are recognized by the system.
    GearTypes
    This enum represents is used to represent the set of valid gear states that the car can be in.
